'difficult' for Mr Venables. He ordered Mr Venables to pay Mr Sugar's legal
costs.
Mr Sugar said the search for Mr Venables' replacement would now begin but
this would not be a hurried 'cosmetic' process.
He said he would be talking to the existing team management duo of Mr Doug
Livermore and Mr Ray Clemence, as well as the rest of the players as soon as
they returned from vacation.
The judge said he was aware Venables was popular with fans and players. 'I
have seen 700 letters expressing support for him and dismay at the prospect
that he may leave,' he said.
Teddy Sheringham, the Tottenham striker, said he was shocked by the court
ruling. 'To be ousted when he felt on the threshold of something great is a
crying shame.'
